cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on optimizing the quality of experience (QoE) for real-time video delivery in wireless networks, which is a key research area in networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with real-time video delivery and QoE metrics, which are core topics in multimedia research. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes an analytical model to capture all aspects of the playback process of a real-time video stream, which involves information theory concepts such as packet dropping and transmission. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a scheduling policy to satisfy QoE performance requirements, which can be viewed as a control problem in systems and control. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper aims to optimize QoE metrics for real-time video delivery, which is a performance-related problem.
